<para id="element-23"><term>Problem : </term> A boy is riding a cycle with a speed of 5√3 m/s towards east along a straight line. It starts raining with a speed of 15 m/s in the vertical direction. What is the direction of rainfall as seen by the boy.
</para>
<para id="element-24"><term>Solution : </term> Let us denote Earth, boy and rain with symbols A, B and C respectively. The question here provides the velocity of B and C with respect to A (Earth).
</para> 

