<m:mo> = </m:mo>
<m:msub>
<m:mi mathvariant="bold"> v </m:mi>
<m:mrow>
<m:mi> B </m:mi>
<m:mi> A </m:mi>
</m:mrow>
</m:msub>
<m:mo> + </m:mo>
<m:msub>
<m:mi mathvariant="bold"> v </m:mi>
<m:mrow>
<m:mi> C </m:mi>
<m:mi> B </m:mi>
</m:mrow>
</m:msub>
</m:mtd>
</m:mtr>
</m:mtable>
</m:math>
</para>
<para id="element-46">We note that two of the velocities are referred to A. In case, “A” denotes Earth’s reference, then we can conveniently drop the reference. A velocity without reference to any frame shall then mean Earth’s frame of reference.
</para>
<para id="element-47">
<m:math display="block">
<m:mtable columnalign="left">
